 other games you use shift, especially for an archer. The problem now is that if you miss the enemy, you run towards them and with a large bunch of them, this might be a VERY BIG PROBLEM if you have crap armour.<P>Running/Walking = Running should be standard for the game except in certain areas. (e.g. houses - I don't think people like other people running about their houses!) But if you press Shift or Alt (the other one) you can walk whenever you want to.<P>This might be a copy of most games but hey, no one knows who started it and it IS the best system for this<P>------------------<BR>The art of flying is to throw yourself at the ground and miss<p>[This message has been edited by Crythe (edited 22-05-2002).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">LightningLockey</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Exactly!  I don't think I could have said it better myself!<P>------------------<BR><I>LightningLockey</I><BR>"Why do I run so many miles each day?" People often ask me.  I just point to the ogre with the battle axe who is behind me...<P>AOL instant messanger: LightningLockey</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Goemoe</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Honestly I wouldn't like running all the time. I like to enjoy RPGs at a casual pace. After all (and thank you for that!) this is no diablo clone, it's a RPG with a diablos like combat system, but it is much more than combat. <P>This game is not about reaching level 20 in less than 10 hours  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/badsmile.gif"> But a key to run would be much appreciated. <P> <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/cool.gif">Goemoe</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Crythe</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Ve